onnect everything as follows:

MQ135 sensor:

VCC → VBUS pin (Pin 40) — needs full 5V
GND → Any GND pin
AOUT → GP26
DHT22 sensor:

VCC → 3.3V pin (Pin 36)
GND → Any GND pin
DATA → GP15
OLED display:

VCC → 3.3V pin
GND → Any GND pin
SDA → GP4
SCL → GP5
RGB LED:

Red → GP10
Green → GP11
Blue → GP12
GND → Any GND pin
Important: Always connect MQ135 to VBUS not 3.3V. The MQ135 needs 5V to run its internal heater correctly. Connecting it to 3.3V will give wrong readings.

check out the image for finding the GPIO pins of Raspberry PI PICO
